I can’t even put it into words right now but last night was a dream. The energy in the Gershwin Theater was electric and I’m so lucky to have been a part of it. 
📸 by @bruglikas @broadwaybruce_
About last night

“Royce King was the most eligible bachelor in town. I barely knew him. But I was young. I was in love with the idea of love. On the last night of my life, I left a friend's house late. I wasn't far from home. I didn't see who he was until that night. Who they all were... They left me in the street, thinking I was dead. Believe me, I wanted to be. Carlisle found me, he smelled all the blood... Thought he was helping me. I got my revenge on them. One at a time. I saved Royce for last, so he'd know I was coming. I was a little theatrical back then.”
